<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1784,2010]" pageId="11" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1784,1810]" pageId="11" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of male 
<quantity box="[476,570,1784,1810]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Overall color pale yellow, apex of anteclypeus, mesonotal triangles, and abdominal terga brown; crown spots relatively small. Male pygofer and genitalia as described for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2007" box="[1312,1436,1825,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordida">
<emphasis box="[1312,1436,1825,1850]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="38">N. sordida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except aedeagus with gonoduct in lateral view extended diagonally across shaft.
</paragraph>
